law.catch_line: Kentucky Revised Statutes substituted for former laws.
law.text: The provisions of the Kentucky Revised Statutes of 1942 shall be considered as substituted in a continuing way for the provisions of the prior statute laws repealed by the act enacting the Kentucky Revised Statutes.
law.history: Created 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, to make clear the effect of the revision.
